-- Seoul shares inch up on bargain bids, institutions weigh
-- By Christine Kim
-- Tue Mar 11, 2014 02:08AM EDT
-- None



SEOUL, March 11 (Reuters) - Seoul shares rose on Tuesday as retail investors hunted for bargains after a recent decline sparked by worries over a slowdown in China's economy, while institutions and foreigners sold local stocks.

The Korea Composite Stock Price Index (KOSPI) <.KS11> closed up 0.5 percent at 1,963.87 points on Tuesday.